{
  "stem": "10446.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it always depicted Jews with huge hooked noses and, you know, the real anti-Semitic Jewish type, the ones as the anti-Semites painted it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as I said, your friends, former friends wouldn't look at you anymore.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the, the papers became more and more filled with anti-Semitic articles, and we felt more and more uncomfortable.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The climax was reached at Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were very slow in realizing that we had to get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I said before, we had that brewery down in, in the country where everybody was friendly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And everybody reassured us, oh, this is not going to last.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People like you are not affected.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If Hitler knew what was going on, he would stop it immediately.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And things like that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, that we never believed for one minute, but we were optimistic and thought it would blow over.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It couldn't last.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were very late in realizing that we had to get out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One event made it very clear, finally.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My father was accused of Rassenschande, having a relationship with a Gentile woman, which was a completely trumped-up charge.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was taken to the concentration camp of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was in 1937.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Hella and I had just gotten married.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in those days, it was still possible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "People still got out of, of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was there for about a week, four, five days, I guess.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hella and I, we drove to Munich where the headquarters of the Nazi, of SS, the Stormtroopers, was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we spoke to somebody there in full uniform.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In later years, all this would have been impossible.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we pleaded our case and succeeded.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After about four or five days, my father was let go.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That this must be an error.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We would like to know who accused him of that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we tried to prove it couldn't be possible.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had witnesses who did testify that this was most, almost impossible, because this was a village down in the country, and everybody would have known what was going on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they finally let him go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He never said one word about his experiences at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not one word.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just kept silent about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As I said, in those days, we knew several other men who were taken to Dachau and, and set free again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But later on, that became a different story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We're not sure when we met first.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was probably on a tennis court in Nuremberg, and-- but didn't pay much attention, much attention to each other.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We finally got to know us better on a vacation where my wife was together with friends, with her father as a chaperone.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was at the University of Munich at that time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a, a friend of mine was there, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he knew that this whole group was vacationing somewhere in Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, why don't we crash the party and go over there?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I went with him reluctantly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's where we really got to know each other and fell in love, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] then we finally became engaged.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How long did it take before you became engaged?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It took another [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] three, three, four years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The engagement was rather dramatic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hella was ready to emigrate to Argentina to join a cousin of hers with his wife who had gone there previously.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I just couldn't bear the idea of having her go away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The closer the departure date came, the more I realized that I just couldn't let it happen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's when I asked her to marry me, and she said yes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She literally had to unpack her suitcases.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not a figure of speech.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was, she was ready to leave.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we became engaged and got married in Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At that synagogue, you said?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a small affair, because of the circumstances.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "By that time, it was 1937, and you had to be as inconspicuous as possible.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You showed yourself as little as possible in the street.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You couldn't have a nice wedding ceremony at the temple.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, the big temple was closed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was not used, and only the smaller little temple which was next door was in use.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You tried to be as inconspicuous as possible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And as I said, you showed yourself in the street as little as possible.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Nuremberg was-- even though it was a city of almost 400,000, it was still a small town, and everybody knew everybody else, more or less.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And especially the Jews were known.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
